DESCRIPTION:
THE PURPOSE OF THIS AMERICAN RESCUE PLAN FUNDED GRANT IS TO AWARD PARTIAL FUNDS TO GREENTREKS TO DIMINISH THE EFFECTS OF FLOODING AND IMPROVE WATER QUALITY IN THE GERMANTOWN SECTION OF PHILADELPHIA THROUGH A SERIES OF MICRODOCUMENTARIES AND EDUCATIONAL MATERIALS.  GREENTREKS IS A NON-PROFIT MULTIMEDIA AND EDUCATIONAL ORGANIZATION WORKING CLOSELY WITH THE PREDOMINANTLY BLACK NEIGHBORHOODS OF THE GERMANTOWN SECTION OF PHILADELPHIA. THIS PROJECT WILL BUILD UPON THE INITIAL EFFORTS OF THE GERMANTOWN COMMUNITY FLOOD RISK MANAGEMENT TASK FORCE BY COLLABORATING WITH THEIR NETWORK OF PARTNERS TO LEVERAGE CREATIVE COMMUNITY ENGAGEMENT EFFORTS AROUND FLOODING AND CLIMATE CHANGE. THE PROJECT WILL DEVELOP A SERIES OF MICRO-DOCUMENTARIES WHICH SHARE COMMUNITY MEMBERS' STORIES OF BEING IMPACTED BY FLOODS, AND A COMPANION SERIES OF SOLUTION-ORIENTED MULTIMEDIA MATERIALS OUTLINING INDIVIDUAL AND COLLECTIVE WAYS FOR PEOPLE TO BE BETTER PREPARED. THE MATERIALS WILL BE BROADLY DISSEMINATED BY PARTNERS THROUGH SOCIAL MEDIA NETWORKS, WEBSITES, E-NEWSLETTERS, AND COMMUNITY EVENTS. 

WHILE THIS PROJECT PRIMARILY FOCUSES ON FLOODING, A SECONDARY BENEFIT WILL FOCUS ON THE IMPORTANCE OF PROTECTING RESIDENTS DRINKING WATER SUPPLY BY IMPROVING THE ABILITY OF PROJECT PARTNERS TO ENGAGE COMMUNITY MEMBERS IN COMPLEMENTARY DRINKING WATER PROTECTION PROGRAMS SUCH AS WATERSHED CLEAN UPS, HAZARDOUS WASTE REDUCTION EFFORTS, SUPPORTING LOCAL GSI INITIATIVES, AND MORE.  IN ADDITION, HANDWASHING IS A WELL-ACCEPTED APPROACH TO COMBATING THE SPREAD OF COVID-19 AND CLEAN WATER IS NECESSARY FOR THE PROPER WASHING OF HANDS. SDWA 1442 GRANT PROJECTS CONTRIBUTE TO PROVIDING CLEAN WATER FOR HANDWASHING IN COMBATTING THE SPREAD OF COVID-19.

