DISCOVERY AND CREATIVE VISIONING:  WORKING IN TANDEM WITH PROJECT PARTNERS AND THE COMMUNITY, GREENTREKS WILL DEVELOP A SHARED VISION, DEFINE KEY MESSAGES, AND ENSURE MEANINGFUL COMMUNITY INVOLVEMENT IN THE DEVELOPMENT AND DISSEMINATION OF MESSAGES AND MATERIALS, HOLDING INITIAL STAKEHOLDER MEETINGS TO INSURE CONTINUED PARTICIPATION IN THE PLANNING AND IMPLEMENTATION PROCESS;

PRODUCTION AND POST-PRODUCTION:  GREENTREKS PLANS A SERIES OF 5 MICRO-DOCUMENTARIES THAT WILL DEPICT THE PERSONAL FLOOD-RELATED EXPERIENCES OF COMMUNITY MEMBERS THAT WILL HELP OTHERS SIMILARLY SITUATED TO UNDERSTAND THE ISSUES AND THEIR PERSONAL RISK, TO TAKE ACTION, AND TO KNOW WHERE THEY CAN TURN FOR HELP.  ADDITIONALLY, GREENTREKS WILL DEVELOP A SERIES OF MULTIMEDIA MATERIALS TO FURTHER EDUCATE RESIDENTS ABOUT FLOODING, THE CONNECTION TO CLIMATE CHANGE, THE POTENTIAL LONG-TERM SOLUTIONS ENVISIONED FOR THE COMMUNITY, AND IMMEDIATE SHORT TERM OPPORTUNITIES FOR RESIDENTS TO PREPARE AND MINIMIZE RISK.  TO DO THIS, GREENTREKS WILL WORK WITH THEIR PARTNERS TO DEVELOP CONCEPTUAL VISION FOR THE VIDEOS, DEVELOP PRODUCTION ELEMENTS SUCH AS SETTING, ACTIVITIES, INTERVIEWS AND ADDITIONAL MATERIALS, CREATE A TIMETABLE AND MANAGE ALL PRODUCTION DETAILS;

DISSEMINATE THE WORK PRODUCT VIA A SOCIAL MEDIA OUTREACH AND EDUCATION CAMPAIGN:  TO HAVE A SUCCESSFUL EDUCATIONAL OUTREACH EFFORT, YOU NEED QUALITY CONTENT ACROSS ALL PLATFORMS (INSTAGRAM, TWITTER, FACEBOOK, ETC.) AND STREAMING SERVICES (YOUTUBE AND VIMEO) AS WELL AS TARGETED BLOG POSTS AND E-NEWSLETTERS WHERE APPROPRIATE.  IN ADDITION, THE CONTENT WILL ENCOURAGE USER-GENERATED CONTENT-SHARING WHICH WILL BUILD DEEPER ENGAGEMENT IN THE COMMUNITY, BROADENING THE REACH OF THE MESSAGE;

